# File Structure Document

## Directory Structure

| Directory | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `/` | Root directory with configuration files |
| `/src` | Main application source code |
| `/src/handlers` | Telegram bot command and message handlers |
| `/src/services` | External service integrations (OpenAI, etc.) |
| `/src/utils` | Helper functions and utilities |
| `/tests` | Unit and integration tests |
| `/docs` | Project documentation |

## Main Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `main.py` | Application entry point and bot initialization |
| `bot.py` | Telegram bot setup and configuration |
| `config.py` | Configuration management and environment variables |
| `requirements.txt` | Python dependencies list |
| `.env.example` | Example environment variables file |
| `railway.json` | Railway deployment configuration |
| `README.md` | Project documentation and setup instructions |
| `.gitignore` | Git ignore patterns |
| `pyproject.toml` | Python project configuration and Ruff settings |

## Generate New Files Here

When adding new functionality, place files in these directories:

- `/src/handlers/` - New bot command handlers
- `/src/services/` - New external service integrations
- `/src/utils/` - New utility functions
- `/tests/` - New test files
- `/docs/` - New documentation